data.title: TV Shows that air in Germany
data.meta_description: A collection of all TV shows, movies, web series and/or miniseries with at least one fictional queer female, non-binary, or transgender character that were produced in Germany.
data.text:
Alles was zählt

The lives of people at a fictional sports and wellness centre in Essen.

Charité

The series describes the accomplishments of several famous German physicians and scientists at the prestigious Charité hospital in Berlin towards the end of the 19th century.

Crossing Lines

A special crime unit investigates serialized crimes that cross over European borders, to hunt down criminals and bring them to justice.

Dahoam is Dahoam

Stories from the everyday life of the inhabitants of the fictional village Lansing in Bavaria.

Dark

When two children go missing in a small German town, its sinful past is exposed.

Das Boot

An inexperienced U-boat crew has to survive a secret mission and a young German woman is torn between loyalty for her home country and the French resistance in the WWII drama.

Dead End

A father/daughter criminologist team solves a mystery in their hometown.

Deutschland 83

The stakes are high for a rookie spy during the Cold War.

Deutschland 86

Take Two for German spies, now in South Africa.

DRUCK

The life of teenagers in their daily lives in Germany.

Eldorado KaDeWe

The lives of Hedi, Fritzi, Harry and Georg intersect during the takeover of power by the National Socialists.

Frau Jordan Stellt Gleich

Officer Eva Jordan seeks to enforce gender equality and equality in institutions and changing locations such as the fire department or nursing home.
